OL,3,CLaw introduced to strengthen OBR and
OL,4,Cprevent repeat of Truss mini-budget
OL,6,FThe legislation means the Office for
OL,7,FBudget Responsibility (OBR) will have
OL,8,Fnew powers to assess "any single major
OL,9,Ftax and spending announcement, or
OL,10,Fseries of announcements over the
OL,11,Fcourse of a single financial year,
OL,12,Fwhich make permanent tax or spending
OL,13,Fcommitments worth more than 1.0% of
OL,14,Fthe UK's GDP, or around #30 billion",
OL,15,Faccording to the Treasury.
